HEADWORD: Maggiore
<hw>Mag`gio"re</hw> <pr>(m⟦aum⟧d`j⟦omac⟧"r⟦asl⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[It., from L. <ets>major</ets>, compar. of <ets>magnus</ets> great.
See <er>Major</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Greater, in respect to
scales, intervals, etc., when used in opposition to
<contr>minor</contr>; major.</def> <rj><au>Moore (Encyc. of
